            . My brother William is a <rs id="t18280911-131-viclabel682" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-131-victim812 t18280911-131-viclabel682"></join>, and lives in Chiswell-street. On the 5th of July, the prisoner came to the shop, and asked to look at ribbons, which I shewed her; she bought two yards, and paid for them; my brother fetched her back.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-131-person814">
                  JOHN 
                  DAVIS
               <interp inst="t18280911-131-person814" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-131-person814" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-131-person814" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in my brother's shop - my sister was serving the prisoner; I was serving other customers - I cast my eye aside, and saw the prisoner's arm over the drawer; she put her hand into the drawer, then put it down between the counter and herself, and put something into her pocket - she then asked to look at some ribbons, she did the same to that drawer, and walked out; I pursued and brought her back, and found the ribbons on her.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Did you find it at the first search? A. Yes - I asked her for it - she pulled it out, and laid it on the floor, up stairs; it was not what she had bought.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
